# static/app.html is GENERATED from the static/app/ fragments (build.rs via
# crates/app-html-assembler); edit the fragments, never the artifact.
#
# Byte-exactness pins: the artifact must byte-match what the assembler
# produces on every platform, so eol conversion is disabled (-text) for it
# and for the fragments it is built from — a Windows checkout
# (autocrlf=true runners) would otherwise reassemble to different bytes and
# trip the regen gates. `diff` keeps fragment diffs textual even if a
# fragment ever picks up a binary-looking byte, so an accident shows in
# review instead of collapsing to "Binary files differ".
static/app.html -text linguist-generated=true
static/app/** -text diff
# The vault crypto kernel's sha256 is pinned into app.html by the assembler
# and parity-tested against the served bytes — eol conversion would change
# the hash per platform (and churn the regenerated pin on autocrlf runners).
static/vault-kernel.js -text diff
